benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/block - Block an account

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC18, @TC21, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC27 cover successful blocking with valid data and various optional parameters.
Invalid Payload: @TC10 covers malformed JSON; @TC14 covers malicious payload detection.
Missing Data: @TC05 covers blocking when no prior blocking states exist.
Non-Existent Account: @TC06 covers account not found scenario.
Invalid accountId format: @TC07 covers invalid format handling.
Missing Headers: @TC08 covers missing required header.
Missing Request Body: @TC09 covers absence of request body.
Unauthorized Access: @TC11 covers missing authentication token.
Security: @TC13 covers SQL injection attempt, @TC14 covers malicious payload.
Edge Cases: @TC15, @TC16, @TC17 cover empty pluginProperty array, maximum/minimum field lengths.
Extra Parameters: @TC18 tests ignoring extra query parameters.
Performance & Load: @TC19, @TC20, @TC25, @TC26 cover high concurrency, large payloads, and resource utilization.
Plugin Integration: @TC21, @TC22 cover plugin service interaction and unavailability.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC23, @TC24 ensure no duplicate entries and backward compatibility.
Accessibility: @TC27 addresses API documentation and error message accessibility.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify rate limiting.
Concurrency Race Conditions: No explicit tests for race conditions during concurrent updates.
Soft Deletes: No tests address soft deletion behavior if applicable.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling to ensure large dataset responses are managed correctly.
Include scenarios testing authorization and access control, especially for unauthorized users.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system robustness under load.
Add tests for caching headers to confirm proper cache invalidation and validation.
Create race condition tests for concurrent requests modifying the same resource.
If soft delete is supported, add tests to verify soft deletion behavior.
